{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"crude-volumed-scaup","description":"## Why\nR1 (capability probe) and R3 (decomposition-shape) gate on detection power that can only be measured against plans with KNOWN defects. Real plans with seeded mutations give labeled positives; their unmutated originals are controls for the blocking-FP bound (Tricorder <10% trust cliff).\n\n## What\nBuild a seeded-defect benchmark from real cleanly-closed plans (drawn from the E1 outcome corpus): mutate per defect class - (1) absent asserted capability (plan asserts a capability an existing module lacks - the E1-verified miss class), (2) layer-cake split (horizontal DB/backend/frontend children instead of vertical slices), (3) consumed-artifact-without-ordering-edge (child consumes a sibling's artifact with no dependency edge), (4) unnecessary mechanism (change not needed - FixedBench over-action), (5) untagged operational AC (evidence lives outside the codebase, no [operator-attested] tag). Pre-register detection thresholds BEFORE running any detector: the per-class targets in the epic's gate table. Commit mutants + controls + labels under docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/ with generation method documented.\n\n## Scope\n- docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/ (mutant corpus + labels + README documenting mutation method and pre-registered thresholds).\n- A mutation-assembly script under docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/.\n- NO gate/source changes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] >=10 mutants per defect class across the 5 classes, each paired with its unmutated control, committed with labels and the mutation diff.\n- [ ] Thresholds are pre-registered in the README in a commit that precedes any detector run against the corpus (verifiable by commit order).\n- [ ] The benchmark harness runs the CURRENT gate over mutants+controls and records the baseline detection/FP table per class (the reference point every R-row's gate is judged against).\n- [ ] A docs/experiments/ writeup records baseline results and how each gate row consumes them.","id":"d125-b4ce-c57f-4f06","parent_id":"6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"E2: seeded-defect benchmark from real closed plans (5 defect classes + controls)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784143700723210001,"uuid":"2481e7e6-054b-4637-8f2b-b35c4d9a95af"}